<span id="iii.viii.i-p2"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iii.viii.i-p2.1"></span>Chapter I.—</span>*The Parts of the World in
which the Apostles preached Christ.*

<span id="iii.viii.i-p3"></span>1. <span class="c13"><span
id="iii.viii.i-p3.1"></span>Such</span> was the condition of the Jews.
Meanwhile the holy apostles and disciples of our Saviour were dispersed
throughout the world. <span id="fr_562"></span>[563](#fn_562.md)
Parthia, <span id="fr_563"></span>[564](#fn_563.md) according to tradition,
was allotted to Thomas as his field of labor, Scythia <span
id="fr_564"></span>[565](#fn_564.md) to Andrew, <span
id="fr_565"></span>[566](#fn_565.md) and Asia <span
id="fr_566"></span>[567](#fn_566.md) to John, <span
id="fr_567"></span>[568](#fn_567.md) who, after he had lived some time
there, <span id="fr_568"></span>[569](#fn_568.md) died at Ephesus.

<span id="iii.viii.i-p11"></span>2. Peter appears to have preached <span
id="fr_569"></span>[570](#fn_569.md) in Pontus, Galatia, Bithynia,
Cappadocia, and Asia <span id="fr_570"></span>[571](#fn_570.md) to the Jews
of the dispersion. And at last, having come to Rome, he was crucified
head-downwards; <span id="fr_571"></span>[572](#fn_571.md) for he had
requested that he might suffer in this way. What do we need to say
concerning Paul, who preached the Gospel of Christ from Jerusalem to
Illyricum, <span id="fr_572"></span>[573](#fn_572.md) and afterwards
suffered martyrdom in Rome under <span id="page_133">p. 133</span> <span
id="iii.viii.i-Page_133"></span>Nero? <span
id="fr_573"></span>[574](#fn_573.md) These facts are related by Origen in
the third volume of his Commentary on Genesis. <span
id="fr_574"></span>[575](#fn_574.md)

