<span id="iii.viii.i-p14"></span> Origen is the first to record that
Peter was crucified with his head downward, but the tradition afterward
became quite common. It is of course not impossible, but the absence of
any reference to it by earlier Fathers (even by Tertullian, who mentions
the crucifixion), and its decidedly legendary character, render it
exceedingly doubtful.

